"""v3.4.1 — Localised ERROR_CATALOGUE text (label/description/action).

ERROR_CATALOGUE in const.py remains the English-language source of truth
and the fallback for any code/language combination not covered here (a
missing translation degrades to English, never to an empty string).

Architecture note: HA's strings.json/translations/*.json system is for
static UI chrome loaded by the frontend (entity names, config flow text)
— it has no mechanism for translating runtime dict *values* like this
catalogue. This module is therefore a separate, hand-maintained parallel
structure, selected at runtime via get_localized_error_entry() in
const.py using hass.config.language.

To keep 125 error codes with many exact-duplicate English texts (e.g.
"Reboot required" appears for 6 different codes) from requiring the same
translation to be typed out 6 times, translations are declared once per
*unique* English (label, description, action) tuple in _TRANSLATION_GROUPS
below, tagged with every code that shares that exact English text, and
then expanded into the flat per-code ERROR_CATALOGUE_TRANSLATIONS dict
that the rest of the codebase actually reads from.

Translation provenance: German entries were reviewed against the source
English by a German-speaking maintainer. French/Italian/Spanish/
Portuguese/Dutch entries are machine-translated and have NOT been
reviewed by a native speaker of those languages — treat with appropriate
caution, and see the v3.4.1 version-plan entry for the known-limitation
note. Corrections from native speakers are welcome.
"""

